<br>
After what seemed a long search,he found the well,once doing so he stopped his steed and dismounted,then lead it far from the well,once deciding he had gotten his steed far enough away,he reaches into his saddle bag,and pulls out the golden bridle which the great goddess Athena bestowed upon him.<br>
<br>
Bridle in hand,he journies back to the area where the well is located.Taking a good look around,he finds a spot where he would hide.Clenching the golden bridle,he moved to a nice large bush,where he stepped behind,and kneeled.Waiting.<br>
